TCP | IP - Transfer control protocol can be used to transfer files or data through local internet
with out tcp | ip we canâ€™t do anything online and it is a protocol and tcp ip is a communication protocol which allows computers to talk to each other by address is known as ip address
All ip addresses are assigned and getting from the DHCP  
OSI Model is a networking model and it works in reverse order
We have 7 layers in OSI model they are
Layer 1 - Physical
Layer 2 - Datalink
Layer 3 - Network
Layer 4 - Transport
Layer 5 - Session
Layer 6 - Presentation
Layer 7 - Application
